                  "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20 black\">Correct!</p><p>Correct answer is B : Hypovolemic shock<br/><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(230, 0, 0);\">Shock is a&nbsp;life-threatening condition&nbsp;</strong><strong>t</strong>hat occurs when the body is not getting enough blood flow. Lack of blood flow means the cells and organs do not get enough oxygen and nutrients to function properly. Many organs can be damaged as a result. Shock requires immediate treatment and can get worse very rapidly.</p><p>Haemorrhagic or hypovolemic shock. the most common cause of shock in surgical or trauma patient is loss of circulating volume from haemorrhage. Clinical and physiological response to haemorrhage is classified according to the magnitude of volume loss.</p><p>Tips</p><ul><li>Shock with bradycardia-Neurogenic shock</li><li>All shock cause -hypotension</li><li>All shock cause-Tachypnea</li><li>All shock cause-reduce urine out put</li><li>Treat the cause of shock</li></ul>.</p>"
